WARNING! This program is for educational use only and has not been vetted for
correctness, conformity, or undefined behavior. Do not use this in a production
environment.

This code implements a simple SHA256 hashing utility. Clarity over performance
is emphasized. Testing is limited to Intel x86 and Apple Silicon on macOS.
While the code is written in pure C++ and should be portable, no such promise
is made.

The standard being implimented can be found in FIPS PUB 180-4 found at
https://nvlpubs.nist.gov/nistpubs/FIPS/NIST.FIPS.180-4.pdf

To compile the source, simply type:

make

At the command line prompt.

